  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nAfter labeling clusters in a Federation, when you type `kubectl get cluster <your-cluster> --show-labels` the `LABELS` field is empty.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe `LABELS` fiels should contain information about the labels in the cluster\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n1.Create a federation control pane in any Cloud Provider and any DNS provider\r\n2. Label your cluster:\r\n```\r\nkubectl label cluster <cluster-name> key=value\r\n```\r\n3. Get info aboyut the cluster with the `--show-labels` flag:\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubectl get cluster <cluster-name> --show-labels\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote: if you describe it, you see the labels being added:\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubectl describe <cluster-name>\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.8.0\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: anyone\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Ubuntu 16.04\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): Linux\r\n- Install tools: curl\r\n- Others:\r\n",
